# Changelog Standards

## Format
- Use [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format
- Sections: `Added`, `Changed`, `Deprecated`, `Removed`, `Fixed`, `Security`
- Date format: `YYYY-MM-DD`
- Version format: [SemVer](https://semver.org/) — `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`

## Content Rules
- Write for users, not developers — focus on impact
- Group related changes; avoid one-line-per-commit noise
- Use imperative mood: "Add X" not "Added X"
- Link to PRs or issues where helpful
- **NEVER** include internal ticket IDs or raw commit hashes in user-facing changelogs

## Location
- `CHANGELOG.md` at project root
- Update on every release; do not batch multiple releases
- Unreleased section at top for work-in-progress

## Example
```markdown
## [Unreleased]
### Added
- Changelog rule for release consistency

## [1.2.0] - 2026-03-08
### Added
- New `/changelog` command for generating release notes
```
